******
[2] Florida (Hendry County): horse
Date: Wed 24 Nov 2021
Source: Equimanagement [edited]
https://equimanagement.com/news/florida-records-fourth-equine-wnv-case-for-2021


The Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services confirmed a case of West Nile virus (WNV) in Hendry County. The 9-year-old Quarter Horse stallion had onset of clinical signs on [9 Oct 2021] that included depression, fever, head shaking, incoordination, muscle twitching and inability to stand. The horse was confirmed with West Nile virus on [22 Oct 2021]. The unvaccinated stallion is recovering.

For more information about West Nile Virus go to the WNV factsheet at https://equinediseasecc.org/Content/ContentDocs/DiseaseFactsheet_WNV%20Cobranded.pdf

[Byline: Kimberly S. Brown]

